  "prompt": "How long does it take to fluently speak a language?",
  "response": "The time it takes to become fluent in a language varies depending on several factors:\n\n1. Language difficulty\n- Easier languages (for English speakers): 3-6 months\n- Moderately difficult languages: 6-12 months\n- Very difficult languages: 1-2 years\n\n2. Factors affecting learning speed:\n- Prior language learning experience\n- Time dedicated to studying\n- Immersion opportunities\n- Natural language aptitude\n- Learning method\n- Frequency of practice\n\n3. U.S. Foreign Service Institute (FSI) language difficulty categories:\n- Category I (easiest): 24-30 weeks (600-750 class hours)\n- Category II: 36 weeks (900 class hours)\n- Category III: 44 weeks (1100 class hours)\n- Category IV: 88 weeks (2200 class hours)\n- Category V (most difficult): 88+ weeks (2200+ class hours)\n\n4. Recommended practices:\n- Daily practice\n- Immersion experiences\n- Conversation with native speakers\n- Using language learning apps\n- Watching movies/media in target language\n\nFluency is subjective and depends on individual goals and definitions of \"fluent.\"",
